==English==
===Etymology===

L ''paradoxis'' fr Gk ''paradoxi'' literally taking glory

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''paradox'''
#A seemingly [[contradictory]] statement that has the possibility of being [[true]]
#:Example: Moving an article from Wikipedia to Wiktionary could increase the average article length on both wikis.
#A self-contradictory statement
#:Example: This sentence is false.
#{{mathematics}} a conclusion based on [[undefined]] functions
#:Example: (2 x 0) = (3 x 0) therefore (dividing both sides by zero) 2 = 3

